<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 24 at 5:32PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Appomattox,
Campbell, northern Pittsylvania, Bedford, Buckingham, Amherst and
northeastern Franklin Counties and the City of Lynchburg through 630
PM EDT...
At 528 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of thunderstorms
over Coleman Falls, or near Big Island, moving east at 35 mph.
Thunderstorms will continue to develop along the southern end of
this cluster, filling in between Lynchburg and Smith Mountain Lake.
Recreation interests on Smith Mountain Lake should be prepared to
take shelter.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Lynchburg...
Buckingham...
Bedford...
Altavista...
Amherst...
Appomattox...
and Hurt.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
